
Her body shakes violently and Michael pulls her into his chest. Until now, he forgot what it was like to hug his best friend and run his hands through her hair and breath in her scent. Fuck, he completely forgot about her.
"No," Lacey mumbles incoherently, shoving Michael's chest. "No. Apologizing doesn't make anything okay. Just leave, Michael. Stop ruining my life like it's some fucking game," Lacey looks Michael dead in the eye and whispers, "Things were better when you were gone anyway." And with that, she turns and runs, leaving Michael completely and utterly heartbroken.
